26-04-03T13:13:17.417236+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### Leave-One-Out Cross Validation (LOOCV)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"08fd0f46","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T08:41:11.930524Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T08:41:11.929957Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T08:41:11.939525Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T08:41:11.938093Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T08:41:11.930491Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.014494,"end_time":"2026-04-03T13:13:17.464744+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-03T13:13:17.45025+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["LOOCV is a special type of **cross validation** where each data point is used once as a test set.\n","\n","\n","- If you have **N data points**:\n","  - The model is trained **N times**\n","  - Each time:\n","    - **1 data point** is used for testing\n","    - Remaining **N-1 data points** are used for training\n","\n","\n","### Example:\n","For 5 data points:\n","- Train on 4, test on 1 → repeat 5 times\n","\n","\n","### Why it is used:\n","- Uses **maximum data for training**\n","- Gives a **very accurate estimate** of model performance\n","\n","\n","### Advantages:\n","- Low bias (very reliable evaluation)\n","\n","\n","### Disadvantages:\n","- Very **slow and computationally expensive**\n","- Not suitable for large datasets\n","\n","\n","### Summary:\n","- Special case of K-Fold where **K = N**\n","- Best for **small datasets**"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":14,"id":"4c1de1c3","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-03T13:13:17.486496Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-03T13:13:17.485969Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.761759Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.760982Z"},"papermill":{"duration":236.306428,"end_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.781049+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-03T13:13:17.474621+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["LOO R²: -0.0030141464920354633\n"]}],"source":["# from sklearn.model_selection import LeaveOneOut\n","from sklearn.model_selection import LeaveOneOut, cross_val_predict\n","\n","\n","loo=LeaveOneOut()\n","model = LinearRegression()\n","\n","#scores=cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv=loo, scoring='r2')  \n","#We can’t directly use R² on single-sample test sets,\n","\n","y_pred = cross_val_predict(model, X, y, cv=loo)\n","\n","r2 = r2_score(y, y_pred)\n","print(\"LOO R²:\", r2)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"0abc0126","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T08:59:42.855544Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T08:59:42.855211Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T08:59:42.859857Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T08:59:42.859026Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T08:59:42.855519Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.016548,"end_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.814404+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.797856+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### Stratified Cross Validation"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"30cb205d","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T09:00:28.099528Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T09:00:28.099211Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T09:00:28.107585Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T09:00:28.105782Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T09:00:28.099501Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.016535,"end_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.84776+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.831225+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["Stratified Cross Validation is used mainly in **classification problems** to ensure that each fold **preserves the same proportion of classes** as the original dataset.\n","\n","1. The dataset is split into **K folds**.\n","2. Each fold contains roughly the **same percentage of samples from each class** as the full dataset.\n","3. The model is trained K times:\n","   - Each time, K-1 folds are used for training\n","   - The remaining fold is used for testing\n","\n","### Why use it:\n","- Prevents **class imbalance** issues in evaluation\n","- Ensures more **reliable performance metrics**, especially for skewed datasets\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":15,"id":"2be7e4e6","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.872734Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.872406Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.875628Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.875024Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.016274,"end_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.877382+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.861108+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["#Stratified Cross Validation is generally not used for regression."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"82215737","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.00985,"end_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.897364+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.887514+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### K-Fold Cross Validation"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"608307df","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T09:03:21.848615Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T09:03:21.848284Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T09:03:21.857937Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T09:03:21.856509Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-02T09:03:21.848589Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.009893,"end_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.917672+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-03T13:17:13.907779+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["\n","\n","K-Fold Cross Validation is a widely used technique to evaluate a machine learning model’s performance more reliably than a single train-test split.\n","### How it works:\n","1. Split the dataset into **K equal parts (folds)**.\n","2. Train the model **K times**:\n","   - Each time, use **K-1 folds for training**\n","   - Use the **remaining fold for testing**\n","3. Repeat until **each fold has been used once as the test set**.\n","\n",